\cf7 This is altogether different from how XR controllers are configured today.\
Though it is a simple change, it can always be adapted to each technology\
specific to its own circumstances.  Bimodal control theory is not a \
consumer product formula but rather a principle of user interaction that emphasizes\
the importance of balanced input roles.  For technologies and products to be finished \
they require more development past the initial separation of roles that we demonstrate\
in the vector-drawing demo.  Additionally, there are many directions to take\
bimodal control theory in any given circumstance and not everyone will take\
the same path.  Yet this is the foundational theory that explains how our current \
interaction devices and UIs are unsatisfactory today and how they can look \
to history to emulate other machines.  Consumer hardware interfaces and software \
leave the user feeling that something is slightly off; neither the mouse nor\
the touchscreen tablet is something people feel comfortable with completely.\
