\f7\b \cf9 The Mouse\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf7 Noctivagous explains with the vector-drawing demo that the mouse should\'a0be \
reconfigured to follow the same\'a0principles as the portable musical instrument.\'a0 \
The mouse is used today\'a0it places too much cognitive load on the \
computer user by combining, into a\'a0single device, at a single location\
steering and triggering of functionality.\cf9  The mouse assigns all of that to one hand.\'a0 \
The reason that happened is the mouse\'a0has always been treated as if it should\
be a direct extension of the hand.
\f7\b \'a0 
\f4\b0 But in actuality, when there is machine \
interaction\'a0this merits a separation of roles, just like a portable musical instrument.\
\
