\f7\b Multi-Touch Devices\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa480\qj\partightenfactor0

\f4\b0 \cf9 In the same way that the mouse is made to work in tandem with a separate location for click-buttons, \
Noctivagous explains in a different essay how to apply bimodal/dual-input to multi-touch tablets. \
First, a vertical list of LED-screen-backed buttons has been provided to the sides of the\
touchscreen.  They are backed by LED displays (just like on Loupedeck or Streamdeck) \
so that they can swap out functionality.  In this circumstance, they will immediately expand the range of \
multi-touch devices because they serve to define the touch\'92s functionality before it occurs, \
following the dual-input principle.\'a0 \'a0For example, a button can be provided to the user as \
\'93fill shapes\'94.  Pressing this button sets up every touch to apply this function.  \
Here is one example procedure:\
\
\'97 1. an LED-screen-backed button is pressed by the user for \'93fill shapes\'94. The touch is now \
defined as \'93fill shapes\'94.\
\'97 2. Any shape finger touches will be filled with the current color until the LED-backed button is\
pressed again or a different button is pressed.\
\
This is a much faster user interface than digging into the menus of the app on the screen, as the\
purpose of the touch is defined by the user as part of using the device.\
\
Here is the situation again:\
\
\'97 1. an LED-screen-backed button is pressed for \'93delete\'94. The touch is now defined as \'93delete\'94.\
\'97 2. Any object the finger touches will be deleted from inside the app or page until the \'93delete\'94 \
LED-backed button is pressed again or a different button is pressed.\
\
This expands the range of what a touch does from the outset whereas currently \
a touch means nothing specifically and to make it do more menus have to appear\
or secondary processes like holding down for more than 1 second.\
In the case of any function, like \'93delete,\'94 it makes affecting many objects on \
screen a rapid process.\
\
A columns of LED-screen-backed buttons can offer many functions like this. \
This is one aspect of upgrading a multi-touch tablet.  Of course, some buttons \
might be fixed on the tablet that are used regularly, such as \'93Escape\'94 and \'93Undo\'94.\
A bimodal setup is available as soon as hardware buttons complement the\
touchscreen and affect its input.\
\
In the same way, other specialized hardware categories, like stylus and tablet for 2D \
and 3D artists, can incorporate a column of buttons to the side so that the user can \
change what the stylus does in real time without stopping abruptly to enter software \
menus or panels.  This is also a benefit of bimodal, that such interruptions have been \
prevented.\
\
There is much room for improvement for all instances of interaction with a computer,\
including mouse, VR, and touch mobile devices. They can be altered for the better with\'a0\
bimodal control / dual-input theory.  The page for this is located at\'a0{\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://noctivagous.github.io/bimodal/"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 \ul \ulc4 noctivagous.github.io/bimodal/}}.\
